

# Check Docker image access for a node

SSH into node, then run: 

$ url -s "http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/instance/service-accounts/default/token" -H "Metadata-Flavor: Google"

Take the token and then run this:

crictl pull --creds "oauth2accesstoken:<ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE>" <IMAGE_LOCATION:TAG>



# Check Audit Logs for changes to the infrastructure

The query below roughly works to get only changes done by humans and filter out read operations:

```
-protoPayload.authorizationInfo.permissionType=("DATA_READ" or "ADMIN_READ")
protoPayload.authenticationInfo.principalEmail!~".gserviceaccount.com$"
protoPayload.authenticationInfo.principalEmail!~"system:.*"
-protoPayload.authenticationInfo.principalEmail=""
protoPayload.authenticationInfo.principalSubject!~"serviceAccount:.*"
-protoPayload.methodName="jobservice.jobcompleted"
-protoPayload.authenticationInfo.principalEmail="system@google.com"
```
